All isolates were grouped into field populations according to their source. GenAlEx 6.5 [48] was used to perform an AMOVA analysis across the 1129 SNP loci with 1000 permutations. The principle coordinate analysis (PCoA) included 213 isolates from 13 field populations. The matrix of pairwise population differentiation was visualized using the R package heatmap3. The All Admixture model was implemented in Structure [49] with 5000 burned-in iterations and 2000 Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) iterations. The proposed number of populations was set to 13 with 100 permutations each. The maximum number of subpopulations was predicted using the formula [50]:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
